50|$|Asylums <b>for</b> <b>the</b> Industrious <b>Blind</b> were {{established}} in Edinburgh and Bristol in 1765, but the first school anywhere, to expressly teach <b>the</b> <b>blind</b> {{was set up by}} Henry Dannett in Liverpool as <b>the</b> School <b>for</b> <b>the</b> Instruction of <b>the</b> Indigent <b>Blind.</b> It taught <b>the</b> <b>blind</b> children skills in manual crafts although there was no formal education as such. Other institutions set up at that time were: <b>the</b> School <b>for</b> <b>the</b> Indigent <b>Blind</b> in London and the Asylum and School <b>for</b> <b>the</b> Indigent <b>Blind</b> at Norwich.|$|R
