5|$|The Royal National College <b>for</b> <b>the</b> <b>Blind</b> (RNC) is a co-educational {{specialist}} residential {{college of}} further education {{based in the}} English city of Hereford. Students who attend the college are aged over 16 and blind or partially sighted. They can study {{a wide range of}} qualifications at RNC, from academic subjects such as English and mathematics to more vocational topics such as performing arts. Alongside regular further education subjects and vocational training, the College offers training in mobility, independent living and personal development.|$|E
